This paper deals with the classification of online comments, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The focus is on the preprocessing of text data before feeding it to machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. The paper also involves the use of machine learning models, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of data and model performance, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
